result.execSummary:
The defendant Johnathon T Robinson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Attempt Attempt Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Defendant Johnathon T Robinson in court with attorney Richard Henry Hart.  Joanne L Hardtke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the state, defense counsel and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, consecutive to Count #2. 
Credit for 7 days time served. 

AS TO COUNT 2:  Defendant sentenced to serve 4-1/2 MONTHS at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, consecutive to Count #1. 
Credit for ZERO days time served.

COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 years under the supervision of the Wisconsin Department of Corrections.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2): 
* Comply with the standard rules of probation.
* SERVE 120 DAYS "condition time" at the House of Corrections with release privileges for Day Reporting Center purposes only - STAYED until 04-29-2015 at 12:00 PM.
* No contact with the victims, Steven V and Karen L.
* Take all prescribed medications.
* Cooperate and participate with a mental health evaluation and follow any recommended treatment.
* Cooperate and participate with an AODA assessment and follow any recommended treatment.
* Maintain absolute sobriety and submit to random urine screens.
* PAY DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY restitution in the amount of $2,112.10 JOINT & SEVERAL with the co-actor, Dominic Robinson (15CF000003) payable to the victims, Steven V. and Karen L. - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
 
Appeal rights given.

Defendant Johnathon T Robinson in court with attorney Richard Henry Hart.  Joanne L Hardtke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Upon State's motion and pursuant to negotiations, Court ordered Count #1 AMENDED to two misdemeanors as follows:

Count 1:  Criminal Damage to Property as a Party to a Crime [a Class A MISDEMEANOR], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 943.01, 939.05.

Count 2:  Attempted Theft as a Party to a Crime [a Class A MISDEMEANOR], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 943.20(1)(a) and (3)(a), 939.32, 939.05.

**NO AMENDED INFORMATION FILED.

AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2:    Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
